        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 1:02PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 102 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 2 miles northwest of Scipio to 4 miles north of
Stuart to 4 miles south of Calvin. Movement was southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.

Locations in or near the path include...
Arpelar...                        Mcalester...
Pittsburg...                      Kiowa...
Haywood...                        Dow...
Bache...                          Mcalester Regional Airport...
Krebs...                          Alderson...
Scipio...                         Blanco...
Savanna...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
